# Caddy reverse proxy for the feed generator.
#
# Terminates HTTPS for your feed hostname and forwards to the local feed
# service (bound to 127.0.0.1:3020). Caddy is the ONLY internet-facing process.
#
# Cert issuance uses the TLS-ALPN-01 challenge (over port 443) because port 80
# is often occupied on a home network (router page, etc.); that's why the HTTP
# challenge is disabled below.
#
# Prereqs before starting Caddy (so ACME can reach :443):
#   1. DNS: point your hostname at your public IP (e.g. a CNAME to your
#      dynamic-DNS host)
#   2. Router: forward external TCP 443 -> this machine's reserved LAN IP
#   3. (optional) add `email you@example.com` inside the acme block below for
#      certificate-expiry notices
#
# Run (from this folder, elevated so it can bind :443):
#   caddy run --config ./Caddyfile
#
# Replace the hostname below with your own.

feeds.chasecrawford.dev {
	tls {
		issuer acme {
			disable_http_challenge
		}
	}

	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:3020

	log {
		output file ./caddy-access.log
	}
}
